name: Reserve
internal_notes: This represents the service where users can schedule Uber rides in advance, for example airports.

name: UberX
internal_notes: The main and most popular service. Allows a user to order an Uber ride. This is the staple product.

name: Comfort
internal_notes: Comfort offers riders extra legroom and highly-rated drivers. A premium version of UberX without luxury pricing.

name: Uber Share
internal_notes: Riders can share trips with others heading in the same direction. Optimized for affordability and sustainability.

name: Wait and Save
internal_notes: Users wait longer for a cheaper ride. Useful when riders aren't in a rush but want to save money.

name: Uber Eats
internal_notes: Uber's food delivery platform. Allows users to browse menus, order meals, and track deliveries in real time.

name: Uber Groceries
internal_notes: Grocery delivery service via Uber. Partnered with major retailers and local stores. Focused on everyday essentials.

name: Courier
internal_notes: Point-to-point delivery service for sending items like packages, keys, documents, or personal belongings.

name: Flowers
internal_notes: Uber’s on-demand flower delivery offering. Perfect for birthdays, anniversaries, and surprises.

name: Pet Supplies
internal_notes: Pet-related delivery service. Covers food, toys, grooming, and other essentials for cats, dogs, and other pets.

name: High Capacity Vehicle
internal_notes: Also referred to as HCV or shuttle. Supports transporting large groups, ideal for events, airports, and teams.

name: Alcohol Delivery
internal_notes: Regulated delivery service for age-restricted items. User must verify age at checkout and/or delivery.

name: Hourly
internal_notes: Flexible service for users who want to keep a driver with them for errands, meetings, or multi-stop plans.
